I can guide you, but I need to correct one important thing first so you don’t lose time:

The earlier “TAO ArcFace” outline was conceptual. Exact TAO commands/model names vary by TAO release, and some versions do not expose a ready-made “ArcFace” command exactly as written. For a setup you can actually execute end-to-end today, the more practical NVIDIA path is:

Train/export with PyTorch → TensorRT (NVIDIA acceleration)

This gives you the same ArcFace-style pipeline, with fewer TAO-version pitfalls.

