Step 4 — Export FaceNet to ONNX

Create:

export_model.py
import torch
from facenet_pytorch import InceptionResnetV1

print("Loading model...")

model = InceptionResnetV1(
    pretrained='vggface2'
).eval().cuda()

dummy_input = torch.randn(
    1,3,160,160
).cuda()

print("Exporting ONNX...")

torch.onnx.export(
    model,
    dummy_input,
    "facenet.onnx",
    input_names=["input"],
    output_names=["embedding"],
    opset_version=11
)

print("Done.")

Run:

python export_model.py

Should create:

facenet.onnx
Step 5 — Install TensorRT

If not already:

sudo apt install tensorrt

Verify:

trtexec --help
Step 6 — Build TensorRT engine

Run:

trtexec \
 --onnx=facenet.onnx \
 --saveEngine=facenet.trt \
 --fp16

Creates:

